Packages and Data

setwd("~/Desktop/Great Graphs/Great Graphs")
library(tidyverse)
df <- read.csv("storms19.csv") %>%
  select(STATE,YEAR,EVENT_TYPE,DAMAGE_PROPERTY,MONTH_NAME)




## Isolating 3 States
dfst <- filter(df,STATE %in% c("WISCONSIN","ILLINOIS","ARKANSAS")) %>%
  droplevels()


## Filtering events
evf <- filter(dfst,EVENT_TYPE %in% c("Flash Flood","Hail","Thunderstorm Wind","Winter Storm","Tornado")) %>%
  droplevels()

dd <- read.csv("storms19.csv") %>%
  select(STATE,YEAR,EVENT_TYPE,MONTH_NAME,CZ_NAME)

wid <- filter(dd,STATE %in% c("WISCONSIN")) %>%
  droplevels()


wif <- filter(wid,EVENT_TYPE %in% c("Hail","Heavy Snow","Thunderstorm Wind","Extreme Cold/Wind Chill","Lakeshore Flood")) %>%
  droplevels()

wic <- filter(wif,CZ_NAME %in% c("BAYFIELD")) %>%
  droplevels()
theb <- theme_bw() +
  theme(plot.title=element_text(face="bold",size=rel(1.5)),
        axis.title=element_text(face="bold",size=rel(1.25))) +
  theme(panel.grid.major.y=element_blank(),
        panel.grid.minor.y=element_blank()) +
  theme(plot.title=element_text(color="white"),
        plot.caption=element_text(color="white")) +
  theme(panel.grid.major=element_line(color="gray30")) +
  theme(plot.background=element_rect(fill="gray5")) +
  theme(panel.grid.minor=element_line(color="gray30",linetype="dotted")) +
  theme(axis.text=element_text(color="white"),
        axis.title=element_text(color="white")) +
  theme(panel.background=element_rect(fill="gray5"))

Number of Storm Types from North to South

clrs <- c("tomato3","cornflowerblue","forestgreen")

ggplot(data=evf,mapping=aes(x=EVENT_TYPE,fill=STATE)) +
  geom_bar() +
  facet_grid(rows=vars(STATE)) +
  theb +
  scale_x_discrete(name="") +
  scale_y_continuous(name="",breaks=seq(0,600,100),expand=expansion(mult=c(0,0.05))) +
  scale_fill_manual(values=clrs) +
  theme(legend.position="none") +
  coord_flip() +
  labs(title="Number of Large Storm 
       Events in 2019",
       caption="Source: https://www.ncdc.noaa.gov")

Bayfield County Storms

ss <- c("skyblue","lemonchiffon1","gray45","royalblue4","darkviolet")

ggplot(data=wic,mapping=aes(x=MONTH_NAME,fill=EVENT_TYPE)) +
  geom_bar() +
  scale_x_discrete(name="",limits=c("December","November","October","September","August","July","June","May","April","March","February","January")) +
  scale_y_continuous(name="",breaks=seq(0,10,1),expand=expansion(mult=c(0,0.05))) +
  scale_fill_manual(values=ss,name="Storm Events") +
  labs(title="Most Occuring Storm Events Per Month",
       subtitle = "Data From Bayfield County (2019)",
       caption="Source: https://www.ncdc.noaa.gov") +
  coord_flip() +
  theb +
  theme(plot.subtitle=element_text(color="white")) +
  theme(panel.background=element_rect(fill="gray5")) +
  theme(plot.background=element_rect(fill="gray9")) +
  theme(legend.background=element_rect(fill="gray5"),
        legend.title=element_text(color="white"),
        legend.text=element_text(color="white")) +
  annotate(geom="label",x="May",y=2.6, size=3,
           label="No results recorded") +
  annotate(geom="segment",x="May",xend="April",y=1.9,yend=1,
           arrow=arrow(length=unit(2,"mm"),type="closed",angle=13),color="white") +
  annotate(geom="segment",x="May",xend="June",y=1.9,yend=1,
           arrow=arrow(length=unit(2,"mm"),type="closed",angle=13),color="white")
